Last week, he signed a bill, the Public Energy Policy Law of Puerto Rico, to power the island solely by renewable energy by 2050.
All of Puerto Rico’s energy woes converged after Hurricane MariaThe past two years have been brutal for the 3 million Americans living in Puerto Rico.
Puerto Rico is betting on renewable energy, but it will be expensiveBefore Hurricane Maria, Puerto Rico generated just 2 percent of its electricity from renewables.
The Trump administration would prefer if Puerto Rico used more natural gasThe federal government, however, isn’t as enthusiastic about Puerto Rico’s commitment to renewable energy.
Federal officials expect that Puerto Rico will receive $82 billion over time in disaster recovery funds, but President Trump has complained about the total amount and blamed Puerto Rico for its financial woes.